node.text:
I teamed up with Kroger to celebrate AAPI Heritage month. I grew up in Michigan and when I would visit my Grandma in Lansing we would shop at Kroger. Little did I know then that Kroger features family owned businesses and have for over thirty years like Monterey Mushrooms 🍄. For this recipe we are featuring two #AAPI owned suppliers! We are making a delicious spinach, fontina (cheese sauce 🤤), and roasted mushroom flatbread highlighting Monterey Mushrooms and FGF Brands. Check out @krogerco for the full recipe 📝

@krogerco #sponsored

node.title: Roasted mushroom, spinach, & fontina cheese sauce flatbread 🍄🤤

node.text: I’ll admit, early on in my career having any “dietary restrictions” walk into the restaurant was an inconvenience; I just didn’t know enough. As we’ve seen our industry change and the needs and wants of so many different ways of eating by our guests, by choice or not, it’s imperative we keep up. I’ve personally learned and continue to learn what it means to feed Everyone. I cook to feed others with the same point of view and that means adapting my food to restrictions, allergies, and personal choices. Being armed with the ingredients that can take the heart of one dish and showcase it in ways that can satisfy everyone is fun for me. Veganism is a way of cooking I am adapting to the most and @floraplantus helps me tremendously. The crème is my personal favorite, it whips just like dairy cream, creates ice-cream just how I am used to, and has the same texture of heavy whipping cream AND it’s made from beans. Whaaaat??!! I recently got in the kitchen with @floraplantus to talk about cooking to feed everyone and to try out their products – tap the post to check out the full video. #FloraChefs #MadeWithFlora #Ad

node.text: So many virtual hangouts happening this year so it’s only fitting that I do one with my friends, who happen to be wildly talented Chefs too. Huge thanks to @patron & @foodandwine for making this all happen and bringing us together over delicious food and a fun cocktail. We are cooking up one of my favorite entertaining meals and a Patrón Anejo cocktail called the “The First Kish”, video demo coming soon. Love and adore you both 😘 @chefbrookew @nyeshajoyce #ad #drinkresponsibly

node.title: Chef Hangout with Brooke and Nyesha 🧡

node.text:
#sponsored A Woman’s Place…is in the kitchen, in a restaurant, as a butcher holding that knife, calling the shots, owning her space, carrying her confidence loudly, lifting up those around by leading through example, leading Her team, inspiring those around her, showing the world what it means to be a woman in this industry and why they call you “Chef.”

I’m thrilled to be working with @KitchenAidUSA to share “A Woman’s Place,” a documentary film and new initiative created with the goal to support and empower emerging women in culinary to bridge the gap as they strive to become leaders in the industry. The documentary short, directed by Academy Award-winner Rayka Zehtabchi, provides a provocative and honest look at the biases and barriers women face in the culinary industry through the stories of three inspiring chefs who are pushing for change in a male-dominated industry in the hopes of making their culinary dreams a reality. The film is available to stream on @Hulu starting today. I encourage everyone, within and outside of the culinary industry, to join me in driving #CulinaryEquality #womensupportingwomen #mentorship

node.text: We have a small but mighty BOH team at Arlo Grey where the ladies are the majority. I came up with a lot of strong women backing me up in kitchens but I also had my share of unfortunate judgment and treatment because of my gender. The most proud I’ve been opening my own restaurant is having amazing and talented women define our kitchen culture and what it means to be the change of the narrative on what a kitchen environment looks like. Pre-covid shutdown we had even more. Past and present kitchen AG ladies - I am SO PROUD of all of you and grateful for your talents, in the kitchen and beyond ✨🙏🏼 #reunitedanditfeelssogood #weloveyoutoochefalex :)

node.text: Home for one whole week. It’s 91 degrees this afternoon. I thought today would be a nice afternoon to do some house stuff…like pull weeds. We have a lawn care company who does ALL of the outside work but decided weed pulling was an activity we should do ourself (Why? I don’t know?). Also, weeds are just green plants, please someone tell me why they need to be pulled!? #iknownothing 🌱🥵 #yayfriday

They say never to meet your idols in person.. I say when that idol is Stephanie Izard you should meet them, become friends, and champion their greatness that they have proven and shown to you time and time again. Long time admirer, great friend over many many years, and forever fan of all things girl and all things goat. So happy for you and your team @girlandthegoatla. A MUST visit - #LA you’re very lucky. Happy opening day Chef and Team!
#yeschef #womeninthekitchen #championthegoodones #topchef #winners #shef

node.text: #ad I am not shy about my 3 cups of coffee a day. My morning coffee whenever I am at home is my meditation, my hour of “me time”, and the only true routine I have. I miss it when it’s over, look forward to the next morning coffee time, and fully savor every second it takes to drink it. I started using a @nespressousa machine a few years ago – the max effort is deciding which capsule to choose and the max return is me coming alive. I live my life with efficiency at its forefront and for me, Nespresso makes my mornings that much easier. I’ll tell you, and I know so many can relate, I am not capable of much before I have my first couple of cups. This partnership with Nespresso is an extension of what I already do in my day to day and I am SO thrilled to have my personal favorite way of enjoying my coffee at home wanting to partner with me.  Come along for our ride together for 2021! #NespressoPartner
